<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" TextAlignment="Justify"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
This section demonstrates Essential PDF's various support for drawing text in a PDF document.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples with descriptions.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Text Flow</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how large text from a text file can span multiple pages in a PDF document. This sample also explains events that are raised when each page begins and ends.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>RTL Support</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how the text of right-to-left [RTL] languages, like Arabic, can be rendered in a PDF document. It also demonstrates various alignments of text.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Bullets and Lists</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for creating ordered and unordered lists. It also demonstrates how formatting can be applied to those lists.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Multicolumn HTML Text</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for rendering a HTML-formatted string in a multicolumn format.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>